    <div class="body">
        <p>Per documentation at <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.view.helpers.html">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>"If $content is present and not a boolean FALSE, then that content is rendered within the start and close form tags; if $content is a boolean FALSE (the default), only the opening form tag is generated."</p>

<p>This works fine for the standard form view helper but when Dojo is enabled $content is set to '' which prevents only the opening tag from being created. The culprit is in Zend_Dojo_View_Helper_Form.php in function form($id, $attribs = null, $content = false).</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
        if (false === $content) {
            $content = '';
        }
